Prt 1:Yesterday, Jan 26 was Australia Day which turned out to be an awesome day. Not to leave things to the last minute, Andy and I picked up some supplies Weds night about 830pm, hooray for late night shopping. Next morning, Andy rocked up at my place at about 845, Dad dropped us into perth foreshore by 915, so we unloaded Everything out of the car and as the car drove away we realised that we had ALOT of stuff to carry for two people. We had 2x24 pakcs of soft drink, a big rug, and esky, a bag of ice, and 2x unfoldable chairs and our back packs. So that is 9 things between 2 people :S anyway we managed to lug it all down there with burning shoulders. We wandered across the oval and picked a nice spot beneath a tree with shade and a parke bench, which turned out to be the best part of the spot, the extra seating. We played a bit of footy for a while until the guys behind us rocked up. They had a little trouble following instructions and failed in attempts to put their tent up, so we gav them a hand. this turned into us playing cricket with Chad, jason, Germany and a few others for a while and having a good time with them throughout the day. Prt 2:We pretty much sat there chattin for a few hours until I went and met up with Sarah and jamie over at the ferry spot. Walked back to where we were based and no one was there so we went to meet other people. Quickly realising that today would be one huge day of walking and catching up with people :S. Luke, Hodgey and Brad turned up not long after that so we met up with them and played some more cricket and threw the gridieon (very australian sport) aswell as some AFL, everyone else showed up after that and i walked around a bit catching up with people. Got tired about 6pm and decided no more walking so i stayed underneath the tree for the rest of the night. The sky show rocked, bext part being when the let off everything at once, so loud and exciting. doesn't take much to entertain me. Well i started this post this morning before work and now i am finishing it. Had a late night last night and got up at 6 this morning to go to work. Spent the day building a standee so now my fingers are hurting and bleeding. Now is the time for fish and chips at Freo then some Lounge till the wee hours and hopefully some sleep before i go to Pt Walter tomorrow. whew so busy. im off

Went bowling tonight with Enj,Tom, Ali and Kate. Had an awesome awesome time even though i didnt win :( Ali won twice and Enj won once by gettin 2 strikes and and 8 on the last three bowls... 
All in all a good night... soo many nines... it haunts me

I'm back from yet anothre awesome time at mandurah. It is amazing that in a whole week you can do so little.
 Arrived there about 1130 last tues night after work. got up around 9 and went for a surf for a few hours. came home, had lunch, did nothing until dinner. went out at night to the beach. cam home and slept. Now that is about the sum up for every day for the past week. Cool heh.
 the best parts of mandurah is doing nothing, and having no pressure to do anything, just lounging around.
 The highlights of this year would be laying on the beach until about 10, even though we ony did it a couple of times. Playing shoe-cricket in mandurah (best version of cricket: playing with a tennis ball and my shoe). having a Yummy Noodle Box ( you know the typical chinese food out of a box take-away. i thought it was only a myth, but NO it exists!), surfing EVERY morning for a week. and definitley the beach cricket. (edit: Oh and the endless amounts of table tennis played)
 So now i'm hoping im not working for the next few nights so that i can go to the Planet Shakers night rallies which will be awesome no doubt.
 Now to go and give Mokimo a run in the Park.
RB out.

Had a great morning drinking coffee eating donuts with mates. didn't care much for the photos. english wasn't that hard, the class watched the news while i read Akira(awesome manga comic, about 6 in the series). Then i received my intro calc test, i got 21 out of 48 which i was dissapointed in. not the mark but myself, yet exactly what i deserved. i always 'expect' to fail yet never do. This made me feel somewhat humbled. It was actually a nice feeling to fail. to feel like I'm part of the 'game'. i have not failed alot of tests ever. this would maybe be less than my tenth. I think it was a good thing, I'm not upset at all at the mark, it's a good feeling. Yay im one of them :).
Then recieved some news that kinda shook me a little. Not for here but im feeling numb at the moment, not much feeling.

Now i'm learning japanese and talking to toray in Wagga who i havent spoken to in a while. I want to go back there next holidays so bad. good times.

Cyaz

Today in English we were talking about graffiti and vandalism on in our nation, city. Mr Wetmore, coming from South Africa a fairly poor and dis-advantaged country, couldnt understand why people would do things such as violence and so forth in a country that is so rich and prosperous. He has seen a country and termoil and people do not know better or have nothing else to do but vandelise and damage their streets, but with an educated country as we are we really have no reason to result to that kind of things, he said if we pay for him he would take us around, and show us the condition of where he used to live, and then we would really appreciate what we have..
I tend to agree with his views, it made me realise how good we/I really have it. I get upset about little things, about not getting a game, new computer.. etc... but people over there dont have anything... and we really lucky.. Anyway it just opened my eyes to appreciate what I have... but of course that  doesnt mean i dont want more :P I think thats bred into us that we want more, think we need more, and not having anything will help us to rely God more often, i think that more people would be christian and go to heaven in poorer country than richer countries becaus ethey have nothing else to rely on, no toys, games, or even family sometimes so they fully rely on God, no material possessions to get in the way of loving God, meh im babbling and repeating myself, meh im babbling and repeating myself. Must do some autobiography and Chem.. l8er dudes

Had a good day today apart from the three tests i had today, which all went well. Got some birthday presents including $50, jack johnson cd and a yoyo(awesome)and of course.. the most best jacket ever, thanks so much guys for getting me that, some of you may not have seen it but ill be wearing it constantly. 
   The fun started when i got home, went to kt's and got my new mobile phone and mini-bike(both edible) then once i got home i decide to get my jacket straight away. So the next bus to freo was at 3.42 and spose to get there at 4.17(remember those numbers. well set off at 3.35 so i wouldn't miss is, 3.40 3.45 3.50 and still no bus, i got bored, 15 minutes sitting at a bus stop is not my idea of fun, close though. well it finaly arrived at 3.53(i wasnt counting..), FULL of emmanuel students! i hate being on a bus full of foreign scool people, anyway this really annoyed me because someone got off at every stop, every 10m. anyway we got about 15 minutes into the trip and the bus over-heated.. can u believe it, a double-bus full of people breaking down on the side of the road, so we had to wait for 5 mins for it to cool down, 10 minutes past and still no go. so then she(driver) checked it again and apparently the fan-belt broke.. like you wouldn't notice the first time you look! , so about 70-80 people standing on the side of the road waiting for another bus to come, again.. not my idea of fun. so 30 mins later a bus come and we are on the way again, got 10 mins up the road and because we were so damn slow the next schedualed bus actually caught up to us, so they decided to transfer 50 students + me, to the bus behind us. finally we are going again and eventually end up at fremantle... at 5.30!!!(dont add up all the times, im sure they dont add up, but i looked at my watch)anyway 1 hr 15 late... so finally 1 and a half hours later than i imagined i got my jacket! it woz worth it, i found myself a yoyo aswell, a 1337 competition yoyo, dont know how to work it yet but hey, ill learn..so i walked out, back to the busport to go home, and these Iona chicks came up to me and i got some chips off them.. they were using me for my jacket, but yer they were so posh, too delicate, anyway got the bus home, not too many dramas.
    Got home then went out to tea to the Mussel Bar in Freo, best restaurant ever! then after i got a banana split thing from baskin robins which was soo nice, needed to throw up afterwards though.. now im here practicing yoyo and only 2.5 fingers have falling off due to lack of blood.
    In short had a fun bday and thabks again for the jacket, u spent way too much money on me... cause now i gotta spend that much on you.. :P
